=Description=

"Nathan Seidle is a visionary in the open source hardware movement and has taken action by founding his company SparkFun Electronics. SparkFun aims to make the world a better place by educating civilians about the technology they own and providing tools to alter it and build their own. Nathan sits on the board of the Open Source Hardware Association, assisting in the next revolution of business and society.

Nathan coined the term "intellectual property obesity" after looking around at other companies that were obtaining patents and proceed to "no longer innovate". What large companies don't realize is that if your idea is easily copied and sold for profit, it will be sold in the local market. Nathan narrates his discovery of open source hardware: "You come up with the idea and share it with your friends, you can innovate on my idea, and sell it for profit". Open source hardware starts from this premise and adds only one thing: "any future idea will also have to be open." He demonstrates how we can continue to build upon each other's ideas and innovate, in open source hardware, leading to better products and increased value."


